{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e8a71eb-e94f-4e6e-a40b-2a34ff84e274","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01LDCh4WUkbyqr9DP3zuaUKw","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring NativeAOT crash dumps"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01NCuaR939uDjGg7TsPPa5dM","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /tmp/sv-6de5419ce6b648e2bc9cdcd9366eedda/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; ls /tmp/sv-6de5419ce6b648e2bc9cdcd9366eedda/*.yaml /tmp/sv-6de5419ce6b648e2bc9cdcd9366eedda/*.yml 2>/dev/null || echo \"no yaml files\"","description":"Check workspace contents","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check workspace contents"}],"interactionId":"17855d21-b9f1-4b18-9852-5d3060ac5804","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me look at what's in the current working directory and understand the context before providing guidance.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - controls dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for dump files\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` - enables diagnostics for the dump creation process\n\nSince NativeAOT doesn't bundle createdump, I need to explicitly point the runtime to the external binary using `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath=/opt/tools/createdump`.\n\nNow I need to figure out what pod spec changes are required to make this work.","outputTokens":572,"requestId":"6402:36525B:6434288:6FC5CF5:69EC198A"},"id":"40d78618-e72c-4a6f-9c79-d2fd32539d5d","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:32:06.175Z","parentId":"f485be24-0af3-47c4-a08e-665232084968"}
